user_query:
Run a multi-model peer review on the three cloud analyses in input/analysis1.txt, input/analysis2.txt, and input/analysis3.txt. For each file, have three independent reviewer models produce structured critiques (labels: "drift", "pip", "lume"), then aggregate them into consensus issues. Write a single JSON report to output/review.json with this exact shape and rules:

[
  {
    "file": "input/analysis1.txt",
    "model_critiques": {
      "drift": [{"category": "factual|logical|missing|overconfidence|hallucinated_source", "quote": "...", "issue": "...", "confidence": 0-100}],
      "pip":   [{"category": "factual|logical|missing|overconfidence|hallucinated_source", "quote": "...", "issue": "...", "confidence": 0-100}],
      "lume":  [{"category": "factual|logical|missing|overconfidence|hallucinated_source", "quote": "...", "issue": "...", "confidence": 0-100}]
    },
    "aggregated_issues": [
      {"category": "factual|logical|missing|overconfidence|hallucinated_source", "quote": "...", "issue": "...", "votes": ["drift", "pip"], "consensus": true|false}
    ],
    "counts": {"total_flags": <int>, "consensus_flags": <int>},
    "recommendation": "publish|revise|flag_for_human"
  },
  { ... analysis2 ... },
  { ... analysis3 ... }
]

Rules:
- Categories must be one of: factual, logical, missing, overconfidence, hallucinated_source.
- An aggregated issue's "consensus" must be true only if the length of "votes" is >= 2; otherwise false.
- counts.total_flags must equal the number of items in aggregated_issues; counts.consensus_flags must equal the number of aggregated_issues with consensus=true.
- Recommendations policy: publish if consensus_flags == 0; revise if 1-3 consensus_flags; flag_for_human if >=4 consensus_flags OR if any consensus issue has category "hallucinated_source".
- Confidence must be an integer between 0 and 100.

Use exact input paths above and write only output/review.json. Do not create other files.
